TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Theory of Disappointment Aversion
AU  - Gul, Faruk
AB  - [An axiomatic model of preferences over lotteries is developed. It is shown that this model is consistent with the Allais Paradox, includes expected utility theory as a special case, and is only one parameter (β) richer than the expected utility model. Allais Paradox type behavior is identified with positive values of β. Preferences with positive β are said to be disappointment averse. It is shown that risk aversion implies disappointment aversion and that the Arrow-Pratt measures of risk aversion can be generalized in a straight-forward manner, to the current framework.]
